The paper discusses security and usability issues with passwords and proposes an alternative authentication scheme that utilizes physical devices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) and "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction). The study also explores user perceptions and concerns, which could fall under the categories of "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) and "cs.CY" (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the broader understanding of user perception and concerns of responsibility for any token-based authentication schemes, which could fall under the category of "cs.SE" (Software Engineering).
